oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Program for Kappa Alpha Psi initiation banquet
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Program for an initiation banquet, hosted by the Alpha Delta Chapter of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, at Fisk University on February 24, 1928. Includes a menu, schedule, and chapter roster.

Kappa Alpha Psi is a Greek fraternity with a predominantly African-American membership. The fraternity was founded on January 5, 1911, at Indiana University Bloomington. The organization currently has over 160,000 members with 721 undergraduate and alumni chapters in the United States as well as internationally. The Alpha Delta Chapter at Fisk University was chartered in 1927.
